    <text>
        <body>
            <p rend="align(center)">C O P Y</p>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>San Francisco</placeName>
                <date>Dec. 25th 1860</date>
            </p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Revd. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Yours have rolled o'er our heads since we have seen each other,<lb/>
                and supposing that time has cooled down our little differences, I thought I<lb/>
                might venture a line or two, especially on business matters. From time to<lb/> time
                I have had the chance of getting your Occident as it originally appeared.<lb/> I
                should like to get the whole of the series complete, as I am about making a<lb/>
                catalogue of my Library, and would wish the Occident to be in its place. I<lb/>
                would therefore request the favor of your sending me the following to complete<lb/>
                the said numbers. I will not all I have. Vo. 9 lacks Nos. 7-10-11-12.<lb/> Volumes
                10 and 11 are complete sent to me by my son in law <persName>Mr. Nathan
                    Moses</persName>—</p>
            <table cols="3" rows="5">
                <row>
                    <cell>Vol. 12</cell>
                    <cell>lacks only</cell>
                    <cell>No. <hi rend="underline">12</hi></cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>Vol. 13</cell>
                    <cell>“</cell>
                    <cell>Nos. <hi rend="underline">7, 9, 10, 11</hi>.</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>Vol. 14</cell>
                    <cell>“</cell>
                    <cell>Nos. <hi rend="underline">9, 10</hi></cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>Vol. 15</cell>
                    <cell>“</cell>
                    <cell>Nos. <hi rend="underline">1, 8</hi></cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>Vol. 16</cell>
                    <cell>“</cell>
                    <cell>No. <hi rend="underline">1</hi></cell>
                </row>
            </table>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I would also like to have Volumes <hi rend="underline">1</hi>-<hi
                    rend="underline">2</hi>-<hi rend="underline">3</hi>-<hi rend="underline"
                    >4</hi>-<hi rend="underline">5</hi>-<hi rend="underline">6</hi>-<hi
                    rend="underline">7</hi>-<hi rend="underline">8</hi>. complete<lb/> in paper not
                bound. I suppose you will be moderate in the charge as a Brother<lb/> Colleague. If
                you will send the same to me direct as early as possible—at<lb/> the same time I
                wish to subscribe to your new Series upon the same terms that<lb/> I receive all
                periodicals with the usual allowance to the Profession.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I also wish you to send me the following works as per printed
                list<lb/> enclosed, as I should like if possible to introduce them into the
                schools<lb/> here. You will send also the allowance made with prices as printed in
                the<lb/> said list. Sometime ago I addressed a letter to you about these books,
                but<lb/> not hearing from you I imagine the letter did not reach you. I hope this
                will<lb/> meet with more success.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I suppose you receive the “Pacific Messenger” and that you know the
                Editor<lb/> is my son. He was at first associated with <persName>Mr. Bun</persName>
                but the partnership is<lb/> dissolved. All the news of importance in
                    <placeName>California</placeName> you <sic>loern</sic> through the two<lb/>
                “Jewish Periodicals” of this city. I hope you are in the enjoyment of health<lb/>
                and succeeding in your praiseworthy labors. <placeName>California</placeName> is
                improving very much,<lb/> I think the proper spirit of Religion begins to find its
                ways through the<lb/>
                <hi rend="underline"><placeName>El Dorado</placeName></hi>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Hoping to hear soon from you</p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">Believe me</p>
            <p rend="indent(5)">Yours fraternally</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">(Signed) <hi rend="indent(2)"><persName role="author">H. A.
                        Henry</persName></hi>.</p>
        </body>
    </text>
